                <h1>Evaluation information</h1>
     			<p>
     			    In the application, the three major measurements will have the same weight. The average of these marks will then be taken and represented in a graph. Each major measurement will be evaluated independently and according to priorities depending on the age of the child. 
     			    <br/>
                    Moreover, depending on the age of the child, parameters will have either a “high priority” label or a “low priority” label, and if the mark that a child gets in a “high priority” parameter is “Needs Special Support”, the system will automatically send an alert email to parents so they are aware of this and can request further information from teachers ,through the application.
